column5: I have a cottage east of Haliburton that I am going to next week, and was wondering if there was any good lakes for walleye around.  Thank Court

There are a few lakes with walleyes, but they're generally hard to catch.  How far east of hali are you going to be?  Kashagawigamog has eyes, as does that whole chain of lakes. Loon lake, elephant/baptiste.......that's all that comes to mind off the top of my head.  Good luck, they're tough to get.  Sinker
